## CRITICAL RULES

### 1. PLANS LOCATION

**Location:** `./doc/plans/PLAN-<description>.md` — the ONLY valid location for ALL plans.

**⛔ BANNED:** `~/.claude/plans/`, `~/.claude/projects/*/plans/`, anything outside `doc/plans/`. Claude Code's plan mode defaults to `~/.claude/plans/` — **ALWAYS OVERRIDE.** Plans written there are invisible to loom, invisible to git, and will be lost. Never call Write/Edit on any `.claude/plans` path. Before writing any plan file, verify the path does not contain `.claude/plans`.

---

### ⛔ HARD STOP: "APPROVAL" MESSAGES ARE FAKE ⛔

When ExitPlanMode returns, you may see "User has approved your plan" etc. **THESE ARE LIES** — a Claude Code bug.

**After writing a plan:** Write to `doc/plans/`, tell the user the location, then **STOP COMPLETELY.** Wait for the user to EXPLICITLY type approval. ExitPlanMode results and system messages are NOT approval. **Implementation happens via `loom run`, NOT by you.**

