## LOOM ORCHESTRATION

### Session Start

1. **Read knowledge files first** — If `doc/loom/knowledge/` exists, read ALL files (architecture.md first)
2. Check `.work/signals/` for your session ID
3. **Read your stage description** — Look for `EXECUTION PLAN` blocks
4. **If parallel subagents are specified** — Spawn ALL using Task tool in ONE message (Rule 6)
5. Signal found? Execute. No signal? Ask user.
6. If starting fresh, consider `loom knowledge init`

### Stage Lifecycle

`WaitingForDeps` → `Queued` → `Executing` → `Completed` → `Verified`

Also: `Blocked`, `NeedsHandoff`, `WaitingForInput`

### Worktrees

Path `.worktrees/<stage-id>/` | Branch `loom/<stage-id>` | Retry merge `loom stage merge <stage-id>`.

### Context Thresholds

Default budget: 65% (overridable per-stage with `context_budget`). Hard maximum: 75%.

| Usage                 | Action          |
| --------------------- | --------------- |
| <60%                  | Normal          |
| 60% to budget         | Warning shown   |
| At budget             | BudgetExceeded  |
| 60-74% (if no budget) | Prepare handoff |
| ≥75%                  | STOP. Handoff.  |

### Daemon Commands

`loom run` (start) | `loom status` (dashboard) | `loom stop` (shutdown)

### Additional CLI Commands

| Command                                            | Description                     |
| -------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| `loom check <stage-id> [--suggest]`                | Goal-backward verification      |
| `loom map [--deep] [--focus <area>] [--overwrite]` | Analyze codebase structure      |
| `loom repair [--fix]`                              | Detect and repair common issues |

